Puree the tuna, mayonnaise, anchovies, and lemon juice in the bowl of a food processor. Cook the pasta in plenty of boiling salted water until al dente, or firm to the bite, about 10 minutes; drain. Toss the tuna sauce, pasta, onion, celery, parsley, and capers together; spoon into a large serving bowl. Sprinkle the top with tomatoes and black olives.